00:47:50,201 --> 00:47:52,702
The sleigh on the roof,
the eight beautiful reindeer

1037
00:47:52,869 --> 00:47:54,119
and Santa-- Me!

1038
00:47:54,288 --> 00:47:56,039
--going down the "chimbley."

1039
00:47:56,541 --> 00:47:58,375
That's what I wanted them to see.

1040
00:47:58,543 --> 00:48:02,128
They missed the kid, but I got there.
My way.

1041
00:48:03,755 --> 00:48:07,675
That's why you came. Not for Gwen.

1042
00:48:09,762 --> 00:48:12,764
1368 miles, then slight left.

1043
00:48:14,559 --> 00:48:16,016
For the love of Lulu,

1044
00:48:16,184 --> 00:48:18,644
bossed about by Tinpot Tom.

1045
00:48:19,063 --> 00:48:19,728
Dash!

1046
00:48:21,398 --> 00:48:23,108
Try them again.
Keep trying.

1047
00:48:23,275 --> 00:48:25,777
All this for one child.
In 600 million.

1048
00:48:25,945 --> 00:48:27,945
We should turn her off a mo.

1049
00:48:28,114 --> 00:48:29,822
Don't worry, sir. Children are

1050
00:48:29,990 --> 00:48:32,199
stupid. Either it won't know
it got missed

1051
00:48:32,367 --> 00:48:34,994
or it'll think it's been bad.
It's a win-win.

1052
00:48:35,161 --> 00:48:36,954
You missed one?

1053
00:48:37,123 --> 00:48:38,456
A nipper? Cor!

1054
00:48:38,623 --> 00:48:42,460
Ha, ha. What's all this here for
if you miss one?

1055
00:48:42,670 --> 00:48:44,170
Could you please type faster?

1056
00:48:44,880 --> 00:48:46,255
All right.

1057
00:48:47,717 --> 00:48:49,300
COMPUTER:
Systems critical.

1058
00:48:49,467 --> 00:48:50,302
Lead in Christmas.

1059
00:48:57,226 --> 00:48:58,601
ERNIE:
Oops-a-daisy.

1060
00:48:58,768 --> 00:49:00,061
STEVE:
Peter,

1061
00:49:00,605 --> 00:49:02,313
let go of my hand, please.

1062
00:49:02,481 --> 00:49:04,273
PETER:
Yes, sir. Sorry, sir.

1063
00:49:05,150 --> 00:49:06,818
And get me IT.

1064
00:49:07,777 --> 00:49:08,612
[♪♪♪]

1065
00:49:10,864 --> 00:49:12,364
MAN [ON HOHO]:
Descend 1000 feet.

1066
00:49:14,994 --> 00:49:17,871
You are at your destination.
ARTHUR: Yes!

1067
00:49:18,039 --> 00:49:19,706
We did it, we did it!
We did it! Hooray!

1068
00:49:20,666 --> 00:49:21,916
Whoopee-doo.

1069
00:49:22,710 --> 00:49:23,543
In 100 yards,

1070
00:49:23,878 --> 00:49:24,710
turn left.

1071
00:49:25,378 --> 00:49:28,422
Straight ahead, left, right.
You are at your client's dwelling.

1072
00:49:28,590 --> 00:49:29,423
Whoa, whoa!
Hey, steady!

1073
00:49:35,806 --> 00:49:38,016
We made it. I survived!

1074
00:49:39,518 --> 00:49:43,480
I'll walk home, I'll get a boat,
but I am never getting back

1075
00:49:43,648 --> 00:49:47,400
in that crazy flying death trap
ever again!

1076
00:49:47,568 --> 00:49:48,902
[BICYCLE BELL RINGS]

1077
00:49:49,235 --> 00:49:49,902
GRANDSANTA:
Go on.

1078
00:49:50,320 --> 00:49:51,695
Get it over.

1079
00:49:51,864 --> 00:49:53,155
I want my bed.

1080
00:49:54,617 --> 00:49:55,909
What, you're not coming?

1081
00:49:59,079 --> 00:50:00,746
You have to deliver the present.

1082
00:50:01,373 --> 00:50:03,123
You've got your special coat on.

1083
00:50:03,333 --> 00:50:04,793
You're our Santa.

1084
00:50:04,960 --> 00:50:08,045
I said me and Evie could get here,
and we did.

1085
00:50:08,213 --> 00:50:10,547
The rest is just elf work.

1086
00:50:10,715 --> 00:50:12,800
Go on, Festive Freddie,

1087
00:50:12,967 --> 00:50:14,302
sling your hook.

1088
00:50:17,972 --> 00:50:20,349
It doesn't matter
how we got here.

1089
00:50:20,518 --> 00:50:25,063
The sleigh on the roof,
the jingle bells, the eight reindeer.

1090
00:50:25,313 --> 00:50:27,856
Gwen would never have seen that.

1091
00:50:31,987 --> 00:50:32,987
[♪♪♪]

1092
00:50:45,751 --> 00:50:46,458
[ARTHUR SIGHS]

1093
00:50:46,918 --> 00:50:48,585
ARTHUR [WHISPERS]:
I wish Dad could see this.

1094
00:50:49,422 --> 00:50:51,715
It would take such a load off his mind.

1095
00:50:51,882 --> 00:50:54,175
[WHISPERS]
So, what are your orders?

1096
00:50:54,342 --> 00:50:55,385
Hmm?

1097
00:50:55,844 --> 00:50:58,722
You're a Claus.
You give the orders.

1098
00:50:58,889 --> 00:51:01,557
Do I? Oh! Um... Heh.

1099
00:51:01,726 --> 00:51:05,061
I'm just happy being an elf, really.
You know, just part of it all.

1100
00:51:05,353 --> 00:51:06,228
[SIGHS]

1101
00:51:06,731 --> 00:51:08,940
You want to order me
to go through the cat flap?

1102
00:51:09,108 --> 00:51:11,192
Oh! Um... Yes, that's a great idea.

1103
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:15,280
Do you want to tell me to let you in?

1104
00:51:15,447 --> 00:51:17,322
Brilliant. Thank you, Bryony.

1105
00:51:18,367 --> 00:51:19,242
[ALARM BEEPS]

1106
00:51:19,492 --> 00:51:20,617
BRYONY:
And do you want to--?

1107
00:51:20,786 --> 00:51:23,204
Quick!
The alarm? Definitely, yes.

1108
00:51:27,960 --> 00:51:29,960
[♪♪♪]

1109
00:51:55,862 --> 00:51:56,653
Is this

1110
00:51:56,822 --> 00:51:58,030
your first time?

1111
00:52:13,547 --> 00:52:14,963
[BRYONY GASPS]

1112
00:52:15,800 --> 00:52:16,965
[GASPS]

1113
00:52:18,135 --> 00:52:19,302
But--

1114
00:52:22,181 --> 00:52:23,431
[♪♪♪]

1115
00:52:28,436 --> 00:52:29,478
Bryony?

1116
00:52:30,773 --> 00:52:31,898
[ALARM WAILING]

1117
00:52:32,608 --> 00:52:33,273
[BARKING]

1118
00:52:35,443 --> 00:52:36,110
Sorry.

1119
00:52:36,277 --> 00:52:39,072
He likes these slippers
even more than you do!

1120
00:52:46,246 --> 00:52:47,664
Happy Christmas.

1121
00:52:49,583 --> 00:52:51,291
BRYONY [IN NORMAL VOICE]:
When you put the address into

1122
00:52:51,460 --> 00:52:52,835
the HOHO, what did you see?

1123
00:52:53,003 --> 00:52:55,713
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
A list of Trelews.
I just clicked on the first one!

1124
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:58,465
Which was not Trelew, England.

1125
00:52:58,634 --> 00:52:59,759
We're in the wrong Trelew!

1126
00:52:59,927 --> 00:53:00,760
[POLICE SIRENS WAILING]

1127
00:53:02,762 --> 00:53:04,347
[♪♪♪]

1128
00:53:06,724 --> 00:53:08,184
What's going on?!

1129
00:53:09,018 --> 00:53:12,063
They've been watching us.
They've seen Evie.

1130
00:53:12,438 --> 00:53:15,315
It's just like last time.
REPORTER: Governments tonight

1131
00:53:15,483 --> 00:53:18,777
are waking to news of a UFO
traveling the globe at incredible speed.

1132
00:53:18,945 --> 00:53:20,195
BRYONY: That's us!
The clearest

1133
00:53:20,364 --> 00:53:22,532
sighting was at
this tractor dealership

1134
00:53:22,699 --> 00:53:24,617
in Idaho.
Had eyeballs on its feet

1135
00:53:24,784 --> 00:53:28,413
and a pointy little head.
It asked me for a sign.

1136
00:53:28,621 --> 00:53:30,873
BRYONY: We're on the news.
REPORTER: From the trail in Toronto,

1137
00:53:31,041 --> 00:53:33,918
these beings do not appear friendly.
COMPUTER: Rebooting.

1138
00:53:34,920 --> 00:53:36,420
We are online, sir.
WOMAN 1: This is

1139
00:53:36,588 --> 00:53:37,713
Charlotte. Mexican

1140
00:53:37,882 --> 00:53:39,007
police found a furry thing

1141
00:53:39,173 --> 00:53:41,050
trying to mate with a dog.
MAN 1: I have calls

1142
00:53:41,217 --> 00:53:42,844
reporting a steam train flying around.

1143
00:53:43,012 --> 00:53:44,804
MAN 2:
Steam train? Been on the eggnog?

1144
00:53:44,972 --> 00:53:47,599
MAN 3:
It's gone black over Mexico.
This thing's going faster

1145
00:53:47,766 --> 00:53:49,141
than anything we know of.

1146
00:53:49,309 --> 00:53:51,184
STEVE: No.
The herd is now in

1147
00:53:51,353 --> 00:53:54,021
Mozambique's airspace,
threatening the fragile peace

1148
00:53:54,188 --> 00:53:55,440
between the two nations.

1149
00:53:55,648 --> 00:53:59,027
Two billion items delivered, and we
didn't leave a footprint in the snow.

1150
00:53:59,193 --> 00:54:00,360
And now--
DOUG: Sir?

1151
00:54:00,528 --> 00:54:03,114
We have lost 80 percent of our data.

1152
00:54:03,324 --> 00:54:05,074
No, no. We have 18 pulse

1153
00:54:05,242 --> 00:54:09,579
data reservoirs of a trillion terabytes!
Sorry, autosave was off.

1154
00:54:09,746 --> 00:54:11,456
Shall I slap him, sir?
Quite hard?

1155
00:54:11,623 --> 00:54:12,289
DEBORAH:
Sir,

1156
00:54:12,458 --> 00:54:14,708
there's a polar bear on Level 6.

1157
00:54:14,876 --> 00:54:17,170
Sir? Why is
Arthur out there?

1158
00:54:18,130 --> 00:54:19,297
ERNIE:
He missed one.

1159
00:54:19,465 --> 00:54:20,505
A nipper.

1160
00:54:21,050 --> 00:54:22,132
I mean,

1161
00:54:22,300 --> 00:54:24,677
47785BXK.

1162
00:54:24,844 --> 00:54:26,137
[ALL GASP]

1163
00:54:26,764 --> 00:54:27,764
[BARKING]

1164
00:54:28,097 --> 00:54:29,849
Sir, we've got something.

1165
00:54:30,016 --> 00:54:32,559
Bryony Shelfley, it's her HOHO.

1166
00:54:37,273 --> 00:54:38,565
We can still get there.

1167
00:54:38,733 --> 00:54:42,070
We just have to go faster, higher!
You've changed your tune.

1168
00:54:42,237 --> 00:54:43,112
I'm not going anywhere.

1169
00:54:43,864 --> 00:54:44,655
I'm not here!

1170
00:54:45,074 --> 00:54:47,282
ARTHUR:
I've taped myself in! Grandsanta!

1171
00:54:47,576 --> 00:54:48,742
Leave me. It's that

1172
00:54:48,911 --> 00:54:50,536
terrible night all over again.

1173
00:54:50,704 --> 00:54:51,621
What night?

1174
00:54:51,789 --> 00:54:53,373
Last time I took Evie for a spin.

1175
00:54:53,791 --> 00:54:54,539
I didn't know

1176
00:54:54,708 --> 00:54:58,503
it was the Cuban missile crisis!
I nearly started World War Ill.

1177
00:55:00,547 --> 00:55:02,382
BRYONY:
Hold still. Someone has to drive.

1178
00:55:04,092 --> 00:55:04,800
Whoopsie!

1179
00:55:05,510 --> 00:55:06,219
ARTHUR:
Oh, no!

1180
00:55:06,427 --> 00:55:07,135
Fencer!

1181
00:55:07,304 --> 00:55:08,346
Mincer! Come back!

1182
00:55:08,514 --> 00:55:09,179
[SIRENS WAILING]

1183
00:55:10,099 --> 00:55:10,764
Bryony!

1184
00:55:11,766 --> 00:55:12,849
BRYONY:
Hi-yah!

1185
00:55:13,434 --> 00:55:14,268
[ARTHUR SCREAMS]

1186
00:55:16,188 --> 00:55:16,980
ARTHUR:
Grandsanta,

1187
00:55:17,146 --> 00:55:17,813
get here!

1188
00:55:17,981 --> 00:55:20,440
Oi! That's me new hip.

1189
00:55:20,693 --> 00:55:23,402
Please, I'll read you Gwen's letter.

1190
00:55:23,570 --> 00:55:25,028
GRANDSANTA:
Stone-deaf. I'm 136.

1191
00:55:25,197 --> 00:55:26,072
[HOHO CHIMES]

1192
00:55:26,239 --> 00:55:27,864
What's that?
It's Steve.

1193
00:55:28,032 --> 00:55:29,117
Steve!
GRANDSANTA: Tell him

1194
00:55:29,284 --> 00:55:30,117
I'm not here!

1195
00:55:30,284 --> 00:55:32,536
Grandsanta says he's not here.

1196
00:55:32,704 --> 00:55:35,456
Hi. I'm looking for a missing relic.

1197
00:55:35,623 --> 00:55:37,125
Steve, three words.

1198
00:55:37,291 --> 00:55:38,793
Is the first one "help"?
ARTHUR: Yes.

1199
00:55:38,960 --> 00:55:40,628
You can help us, Steve!
It was him!

1200
00:55:40,795 --> 00:55:42,922
Frosty the Madman.
He forced me to come.

1201
00:55:43,090 --> 00:55:44,840
Elf, back me up
if you want a career.

1202
00:55:45,009 --> 00:55:47,300
I forced you?
You see? Look.

1203
00:55:47,469 --> 00:55:49,804
What did you want, Grandsanta?
Let me guess. Hm.

1204
00:55:49,972 --> 00:55:52,597
A picture of you in the sleigh
delivering the gift

1205
00:55:52,766 --> 00:55:54,851
to show me how it's really done?

1206
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:55,684
No.

1207
00:55:55,853 --> 00:55:57,853
You know the picture
they'll have tomorrow?

1208
00:55:58,021 --> 00:55:59,731
You, led away in handcuffs!

1209
00:55:59,898 --> 00:56:02,900
The Santa who was seen.
By everybody on Earth.

1210
00:56:03,110 --> 00:56:05,068
The Santa who ruined Christmas.

1211
00:56:05,237 --> 00:56:06,153
Ruined it!

1212
00:56:06,320 --> 00:56:10,407
We'll fix this, Steve.
We'll be back home in the
wobble of a reindeer's buttocks.

1213
00:56:10,576 --> 00:56:14,411
And Evie can go back in mothballs.
You can forget she ever existed.

1214
00:56:14,579 --> 00:56:17,581
You can't just go home.
What about Gwen?

1215
00:56:17,750 --> 00:56:20,710
Gwen. For that, you'd threaten
my whole operation?

1216
00:56:20,878 --> 00:56:24,172
Steve, you said if there was any way
to get there, you would.

1217
00:56:24,338 --> 00:56:25,882
Well, this is it. Look.

1218
00:56:26,050 --> 00:56:27,382
The old sleigh is perfect!

1219
00:56:27,675 --> 00:56:31,887
Uh, right. Well, anyway, it goes
really fast, even with bits missing.

1220
00:56:32,056 --> 00:56:34,139
And we've got quite a few
reindeer left.

1221
00:56:34,307 --> 00:56:36,976
And, if I'm sick again,
I could be sick in a bag.

1222
00:56:37,143 --> 00:56:38,728
I'll wrap him one.

1223
00:56:39,313 --> 00:56:40,228
We can help them.

1224
00:56:40,396 --> 00:56:41,521
No one missed, sir!

1225
00:56:41,690 --> 00:56:43,565
All correct presents,
present and correct.

1226
00:56:44,485 --> 00:56:46,402
ARTHUR:
If you help us, Steve,

1227
00:56:46,570 --> 00:56:47,862
we can do it!

1228
00:56:52,992 --> 00:56:54,534
THOMAS:
Grandsanta and Arthur would be

1229
00:56:54,702 --> 00:56:56,871
the heroes of the night, sir!

1230
00:56:59,500 --> 00:57:01,291
Come home now!

1231
00:57:01,751 --> 00:57:03,001
If we all just gave in

1232
00:57:03,170 --> 00:57:05,128
to Christmas spirit, there'd be chaos.

1233
00:57:05,422 --> 00:57:07,672
Unh! We're on our way, Steve.
No!

1234
00:57:08,175 --> 00:57:10,134
Santa will want us to get to Gwen.

1235
00:57:10,302 --> 00:57:12,344
Ask him. Please.

1236
00:57:12,512 --> 00:57:13,554
STEVE:
Arthur,

1237
00:57:14,514 --> 00:57:16,974
this is Dad we're talking about.

1238
00:57:17,141 --> 00:57:20,978
There was a time when he cared about
every last gift tag, but now

1239
00:57:21,146 --> 00:57:24,356
he just wants to be loved
and get some rest.

1240
00:57:25,275 --> 00:57:29,987
No. He's lying awake,
worrying his beard off about Gwen.

1241
00:57:30,530 --> 00:57:31,530
[LINE RINGS]

1242
00:57:31,697 --> 00:57:34,242
SANTA:
Ho-ho-ho. Off to the land of nod.

1243
00:57:34,784 --> 00:57:37,369
Please do not disturb
until December 26th.

1244
00:57:37,538 --> 00:57:38,704
Is that it, dear?
MRS. SANTA: Yes.

1245
00:57:38,871 --> 00:57:39,579
Press the red--

1246
00:57:39,748 --> 00:57:40,831
[MACHINE BEEPS]

1247
00:57:42,000 --> 00:57:43,041
No.

1248
00:57:43,668 --> 00:57:46,253
Santa's the most caring man
in the world.

1249
00:57:46,420 --> 00:57:50,007
So why are you here,
not him?

1250
00:57:51,885 --> 00:57:53,052
[GRANDSANTA GRUNTS]

1251
00:57:53,637 --> 00:57:55,012
[ALL SCREAMING]

1252
00:57:56,472 --> 00:57:58,474
[ALL GRUNT]

1253
00:58:13,364 --> 00:58:15,074
Don't leave me, Arthur!

1254
00:58:15,284 --> 00:58:19,536
Poor old man and his reindeer,
on our own at Christmas?

1255
00:58:20,079 --> 00:58:23,916
At least have the decency
to finish us off with a rock!

1256
00:58:35,052 --> 00:58:37,054
[♪♪♪]

1257
00:58:59,327 --> 00:59:01,119
Poor Evie.

1258
00:59:04,498 --> 00:59:06,458
Sun'll be up soon.

1259
00:59:06,626 --> 00:59:08,501
It's Christmas!

1260
00:59:09,128 --> 00:59:12,422
Christmas is for kids.
You grow out of it.

1261
00:59:12,590 --> 00:59:14,257
What, in the last six minutes?

1262
00:59:15,302 --> 00:59:18,054
I know what you all say about me,
you know.

1263
00:59:18,262 --> 00:59:19,137
[SCOFFS]

1264
00:59:19,306 --> 00:59:22,016
[IN HIGH-PITCHED VOICE]
"He belongs in the South Pole."

1265
00:59:22,516 --> 00:59:26,561
[IMITATING SANTA]
"Dear Arthur, what a puzzle."

1266
00:59:26,771 --> 00:59:28,021
[♪♪♪]

1267
00:59:28,273 --> 00:59:29,815
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
Well, you were right.

1268
00:59:30,483 --> 00:59:33,235
All that fuss over one kid.

1269
00:59:33,402 --> 00:59:36,030
I was being ridiculous.

1270
00:59:36,782 --> 00:59:37,489
[SIGHS]

1271
00:59:37,657 --> 00:59:39,449
This is nice.

1272
00:59:39,617 --> 00:59:42,452
It's good to get away from it all,
you know.

1273
00:59:42,621 --> 00:59:44,621
All the Christmas fuss.

1274
00:59:50,003 --> 00:59:51,795
[GRUNTS]

1275
00:59:52,838 --> 00:59:56,467
I'm sorry I messed things up, lad.

1276
00:59:56,927 --> 00:59:58,094
You see,

1277
00:59:58,262 --> 01:00:01,931
the night I last took Evie out

1278
01:00:02,099 --> 01:00:05,184
when there was all that fuss,

1279
01:00:05,393 --> 01:00:07,478
your father came to me.

1280
01:00:07,646 --> 01:00:09,313
I'll never forget it.

1281
01:00:09,481 --> 01:00:11,565
Couldn't look me in the eye.

1282
01:00:11,775 --> 01:00:13,985
"Dad," he says.

1283
01:00:14,402 --> 01:00:17,947
"Steve thinks it best
you don't fly again.

1284
01:00:19,324 --> 01:00:22,034
We're scrapping the sleigh."

1285
01:00:22,994 --> 01:00:25,079
Me own son

1286
01:00:25,746 --> 01:00:28,708
who used to sit where you sat,
looking up at me.

1287
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:34,963
I just wanted them to remember

1288
01:00:35,132 --> 01:00:37,340
who I used to be.

1289
01:00:39,344 --> 01:00:44,139
I was a bit like you, lad.
Keen as cranberry.

1290
01:00:44,307 --> 01:00:46,641
So was your dad.

1291
01:00:47,268 --> 01:00:49,228
You get old, that's all.

1292
01:00:49,396 --> 01:00:52,273
Everything changes.

1293
01:00:52,440 --> 01:00:53,815
Does it?

1294
01:00:55,568 --> 01:01:00,155
How can I ever write another letter
saying that Santa cares?

1295
01:01:00,364 --> 01:01:02,199
[♪♪♪]

1296
01:01:05,579 --> 01:01:07,413
[WAVERING SQUEAL]

1297
01:01:08,373 --> 01:01:09,956
Good night, Dad.

1298
01:01:11,001 --> 01:01:12,418
Sleep well.

1299
01:01:14,128 --> 01:01:15,628
[SANTA SNORES]

1300
01:01:15,797 --> 01:01:16,963
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

1301
01:01:19,967 --> 01:01:21,010
Oh!

1302
01:01:21,510 --> 01:01:25,097
Sir, we know you shouldn't
believe rumors, but we do.

1303
01:01:25,264 --> 01:01:27,016
Is it true you missed a child?

1304
01:01:27,184 --> 01:01:29,351
Me? No, no, no.

1305
01:01:29,518 --> 01:01:31,936
Well, uh, in a way, yes.

1306
01:01:32,105 --> 01:01:33,313
[ALL GASP]

1307
01:01:33,815 --> 01:01:35,065
It was just one.

1308
01:01:35,233 --> 01:01:37,068
In fact, not even that.

1309
01:01:37,235 --> 01:01:39,277
Naught point lots more naughts,

1310
01:01:39,445 --> 01:01:42,155
then a number
and some sort of percent at the end.

1311
01:01:42,324 --> 01:01:45,617
Not really an error, just a one.

1312
01:01:45,786 --> 01:01:48,411
One child doesn't matter?
Which one?

1313
01:01:48,579 --> 01:01:49,996
Well, I... It's not that--

1314
01:01:50,164 --> 01:01:51,998
SEB:
I did nine ones in Greece.

1315
01:01:52,166 --> 01:01:53,751
Did those matter?
FERGUS: What about my ones

1316
01:01:53,918 --> 01:01:56,086
in Germany? One of them was twins!

1317
01:01:56,253 --> 01:01:58,005
They don't matter half each.

1318
01:01:58,172 --> 01:02:02,467
Um... Why don't you ask Steve?
He can explain. Fiendishly clever.

1319
01:02:02,635 --> 01:02:04,719
But aren't you in charge, sir?

1320
01:02:05,262 --> 01:02:08,766
Of course. I'm Santa.

1321
01:02:08,934 --> 01:02:09,766
THOMAS:
Sir,

1322
01:02:09,934 --> 01:02:12,936
if the one that got missed
doesn't matter,

1323
01:02:13,105 --> 01:02:15,898
why have Arthur and Grandsanta
gone to take it?

1324
01:02:16,190 --> 01:02:20,985
What?
Malcolm, what's this about Arthur?

1325
01:02:21,570 --> 01:02:22,862
[ELVES CLAMORING]

1326
01:02:23,114 --> 01:02:24,114
ELF 1:
He's crazy.

1327
01:02:24,282 --> 01:02:26,492
DEBORAH:
Is there a list of children
who don't matter?

1328
01:02:26,659 --> 01:02:28,786
Santa said they don't matter
100 percent.

1329
01:02:28,954 --> 01:02:31,831
ELF 2:
Is it true children aren't real,
they're just antimatter?

1330
01:02:32,206 --> 01:02:34,250
Shh, shh! Do not-- Look. Look!

1331
01:02:34,418 --> 01:02:38,086
I festivized every single country
in the world. You see?

1332
01:02:38,255 --> 01:02:40,755
This one, this one, this one.
All of them.

1333
01:02:40,923 --> 01:02:44,135
I mean, who cares about
one single tiny child?

1334
01:02:44,302 --> 01:02:45,427
[ALL GASP]

1335
01:02:47,097 --> 01:02:49,139
Uh... I do.

1336
01:02:50,057 --> 01:02:51,474
Arthur.

1337
01:02:51,726 --> 01:02:53,853
My poor boy.

1338
01:02:54,103 --> 01:02:55,980
Why on earth would he--?

1339
01:02:56,690 --> 01:03:00,150
You're his brother, Steve.
How could you let him?

1340
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:04,320
And about this child you missed,

1341
01:03:04,489 --> 01:03:07,157
I'm really not sure
you made the right decision.

1342
01:03:09,536 --> 01:03:11,954
Is that bird doo
on your shoulder?

1343
01:03:12,706 --> 01:03:13,914
Right.

1344
01:03:14,081 --> 01:03:15,541
Over there is Satellite

1345
01:03:15,708 --> 01:03:18,168
Tracking, Navigation, Data Analysis.

1346
01:03:18,335 --> 01:03:22,338
Coffee machine's by the door.
Good night, Santa.

1347
01:03:22,632 --> 01:03:26,135
♪ Gloria ♪

1348
01:03:26,302 --> 01:03:29,012
♪ Hosanna in excelsis ♪♪

1349
01:03:32,641 --> 01:03:33,893
SANTA:
Um...

1350
01:03:35,353 --> 01:03:36,978
I'll be right back.

1351
01:03:41,693 --> 01:03:43,693
[DOOR CLOSES]

1352
01:03:51,827 --> 01:03:53,829
[♪♪♪]

1353
01:04:15,684 --> 01:04:17,603
ARTHUR:
Dear Xiao-Ling,
thanks for your letter

1354
01:04:17,771 --> 01:04:19,980
and drawing of Santa
tripping over your dog.

1355
01:04:20,148 --> 01:04:21,190
It was hilarious.

1356
01:04:21,358 --> 01:04:22,315
Dear Alessandro,

1357
01:04:22,483 --> 01:04:26,612
I'm sorry your family's
had a hard year, but Santa is real.

1358
01:04:26,780 --> 01:04:31,115
Dear Lars,
I promise Santa will come.

1359
01:04:31,284 --> 01:04:33,869
He's the greatest man ever.

1360
01:04:52,722 --> 01:04:54,806
Can I burn this?
Sure.

1361
01:04:54,974 --> 01:04:55,641
[SIGHS]

1362
01:04:55,809 --> 01:04:57,643
There's millions like it.

1363
01:05:15,161 --> 01:05:15,827
[GRUNTS]

1364
01:05:19,791 --> 01:05:21,500
This picture.

1365
01:05:21,793 --> 01:05:23,960
This drawing!

1366
01:05:24,963 --> 01:05:26,880
It isn't of Dad

1367
01:05:27,757 --> 01:05:28,590
or you

1368
01:05:29,175 --> 01:05:30,509
or Steve.

1369
01:05:32,721 --> 01:05:34,554
This is Santa!

1370
01:05:35,347 --> 01:05:36,139
Ha, ha!

1371
01:05:36,307 --> 01:05:41,603
And as long we get the bike to Gwen
before she wakes up, then Santa came!

1372
01:05:42,313 --> 01:05:45,106
And he cares! Ha, ha!

1373
01:05:45,567 --> 01:05:46,692
[PANTING]

1374
01:05:48,652 --> 01:05:50,362
[PLAYING "JINGLE BELLS"]

1375
01:05:50,572 --> 01:05:51,780
Excuse!
Aah!

1376
01:05:51,947 --> 01:05:53,615
ARTHUR:
♪ Jingle bells, jingle bells ♪

1377
01:05:53,782 --> 01:05:55,367
♪ Jingle all the way ♪

1378
01:05:55,534 --> 01:05:56,827
♪ Oh, what fun it is to reach ♪

1379
01:05:56,994 --> 01:05:59,288
♪ Gwen Hines on Christmas Day
Wah-hey! ♪♪

1380
01:06:00,539 --> 01:06:01,831
[ARTHUR GRUNTING]

1381
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:04,208
ARTHUR:
♪ Jingle Bells
This boat smells ♪

1382
01:06:05,170 --> 01:06:07,378
♪ Three thousand miles to go ♪♪

1383
01:06:08,422 --> 01:06:09,715
GRANDSANTA:
Oh, dear.

1384
01:06:10,090 --> 01:06:13,844
I've seen this before.
Sleigh fever, they call it.

1385
01:06:14,012 --> 01:06:16,889
Pressure of Christmas
sends a man doolally-tap.

1386
01:06:17,056 --> 01:06:19,974
Santa Claus XVI got it, 1802.

1387
01:06:20,143 --> 01:06:23,144
Every child that year got a sausage
nailed to a piece of bark.

1388
01:06:23,438 --> 01:06:24,188
Unh! Whoa!

1389
01:06:24,981 --> 01:06:29,568
Arthur, do you really think you can
row the Atlantic Ocean in the next

1390
01:06:29,735 --> 01:06:31,402
37 minutes?
It's not,

1391
01:06:31,570 --> 01:06:34,572
unh, too late yet.

1392
01:06:34,740 --> 01:06:36,492
I just have to keep,

1393
01:06:36,659 --> 01:06:37,909
unh, going.

1394
01:06:38,077 --> 01:06:41,496
We need a blunt instrument.
Knock him out and regroup.

1395
01:06:41,664 --> 01:06:46,460
MAN [ON HOHO]:
Make a legal U-turn,
then slight right in 4228 miles.

1396
01:06:46,628 --> 01:06:49,045
You do know
we're going round in circles?

1397
01:06:49,672 --> 01:06:54,635
You know, we're not the only ones.
Maybe I will see Evie again.

1398
01:06:54,927 --> 01:06:56,637
What do you mean?
GRANDSANTA: Reindeer are

1399
01:06:56,804 --> 01:06:58,389
brave, powerful beasts

1400
01:06:58,556 --> 01:07:01,684
but they're also dappled cretins
with twigs on their heads.

1401
01:07:01,851 --> 01:07:06,355
They'll just keep going
in a straight line
right round the world.

1402
01:07:06,606 --> 01:07:08,898
They'll be way up in the sky, flying

1403
01:07:09,067 --> 01:07:11,610
at unimaginable speed,
but they'll pass

1404
01:07:11,777 --> 01:07:13,778
right over our heads.
Great!

1405
01:07:13,947 --> 01:07:15,655
We can get the sleigh back!

1406
01:07:18,409 --> 01:07:19,409
[♪♪♪]

1407
01:07:19,661 --> 01:07:20,327
Chief De Silva.

1408
01:07:20,911 --> 01:07:23,914
Where is this UFO?
It's circling the Earth, ma'am.

1409
01:07:24,081 --> 01:07:26,708
Nineteen minutes ago,
it went into orbit.

1410
01:07:27,543 --> 01:07:31,045
You? Up there?
Catch that with this?

1411
01:07:32,047 --> 01:07:33,047
Magic dust.

1412
01:07:33,215 --> 01:07:34,757
You crack it over your head.

1413
01:07:34,925 --> 01:07:38,846
You'll have to focus. The sleigh'll be
coming at you at 45,000 miles an hour.

1414
01:07:39,012 --> 01:07:40,764
45,000--?
GRANDSANTA: You'll be torn

1415
01:07:40,931 --> 01:07:41,974
in half!

1416
01:07:42,141 --> 01:07:45,601
Depends on the angle the sleigh hits.
You might just get beheaded.

1417
01:07:45,769 --> 01:07:51,023
I've got a phobia of being beheaded,
and heights and speed and reindeer

1418
01:07:51,192 --> 01:07:52,275
and buttons.

1419
01:07:52,527 --> 01:07:53,568
Buttons?

1420
01:07:53,737 --> 01:07:55,695
Yeah, I'm pretty much scared
of everything.

1421
01:07:55,864 --> 01:07:59,032
Gwen thinks you're coming. Ah!

1422
01:07:59,199 --> 01:08:00,701
You can't do this. Yes, you can!

1423
01:08:00,869 --> 01:08:03,369
No, you can't. Yes, you can!
Come on, Arthur!

1424
01:08:03,538 --> 01:08:05,329
Don't worry. Only a raving lunatic--

1425
01:08:05,498 --> 01:08:07,791
I have to worry!
It's the only thing I'm good at!

1426
01:08:07,958 --> 01:08:08,958
[GASPS]

1427
01:08:09,126 --> 01:08:10,168
Worry me.

1428
01:08:10,335 --> 01:08:11,961
The sleigh'll be back
any minute.

1429
01:08:12,130 --> 01:08:13,755
Come on. Worry me, quickly!

1430
01:08:14,798 --> 01:08:17,341
Imagine Gwen, all alone,

1431
01:08:17,510 --> 01:08:20,011
nothing under the tree.
Here we go. Unh.

1432
01:08:20,637 --> 01:08:21,305
[YELLS]

1433
01:08:21,472 --> 01:08:22,847
No! Don't like this! Stop! Stop! Stop!

1434
01:08:23,015 --> 01:08:23,849
Get me down!

1435
01:08:24,016 --> 01:08:25,475
The tears as she finds
she's been left out.

1436
01:08:26,269 --> 01:08:28,353
Screaming, "Santa didn't come!"

1437
01:08:28,520 --> 01:08:29,520
Oh, Gwen.

1438
01:08:29,689 --> 01:08:31,481
No! It's just

1439
01:08:31,649 --> 01:08:33,775
too high!
BRYONY: Gwen in the street

1440
01:08:33,984 --> 01:08:36,069
surrounded by kids
on new bikes, pointing:

1441
01:08:36,488 --> 01:08:39,323
"That's the girl
that Santa hates!"

1442
01:08:39,490 --> 01:08:43,618
She runs away,
alcoholic by the age of 9.
Dead before she's even--!

1443
01:08:43,787 --> 01:08:46,371
She may never build
a snowman again!

1444
01:08:46,538 --> 01:08:47,413
[ARTHUR YELLS]

1445
01:08:47,748 --> 01:08:50,792
What if there are buttons on the sleigh
I don't know about?!

1446
01:08:51,002 --> 01:08:53,002
Here it is!

1447
01:09:03,680 --> 01:09:04,806
Um...

1448
01:09:04,974 --> 01:09:05,807
[SCREAMING]

1449
01:09:06,391 --> 01:09:07,684
[♪♪♪]

1450
01:09:12,524 --> 01:09:14,190
How do you think he's, uh...?

1451
01:09:14,359 --> 01:09:17,694
Fine, fine. Probably just, uh...

1452
01:09:17,862 --> 01:09:19,863
[♪♪♪]

1453
01:09:20,030 --> 01:09:21,573
[SCREAMING
AND WHIMPERING]

1454
01:09:28,081 --> 01:09:30,039
[WHISTLING
"GOOD KING WENCESLAS"]

1455
01:09:32,335 --> 01:09:35,671
So how come they didn't
scrap the sleigh, sir?

1456
01:09:35,838 --> 01:09:39,591
I threatened the elves.
Said I'd feed them to the polar bears.

1457
01:09:39,759 --> 01:09:41,009
[CLEARS THROAT]

1458
01:09:43,846 --> 01:09:44,512
Whoa!

1459
01:09:46,474 --> 01:09:47,349
[GRUNTING]

1460
01:09:51,311 --> 01:09:56,274
Elf, how do you fancy being the one
to tell his parents about all this?

1461
01:09:57,569 --> 01:09:58,234
[YELLING]

1462
01:10:04,242 --> 01:10:05,868
[GRUNTS THEN
WHIMPERING AND YELLING]

1463
01:10:10,456 --> 01:10:12,164
Whoa! Whoa!

1464
01:10:12,332 --> 01:10:13,250
Whoa!

1465
01:10:20,841 --> 01:10:22,050
[ARTHUR SCREAMING]

1466
01:10:26,389 --> 01:10:27,055
[BRYONY COUGHING]

1467
01:10:27,222 --> 01:10:28,849
[WHEEZING]

1468
01:10:29,016 --> 01:10:31,560
Yay! Arthur!

1469
01:10:31,728 --> 01:10:33,604
You did it!
I did it with worry!

1470
01:10:33,770 --> 01:10:36,314
Oh, I was sure you'd die.
It was great!

1471
01:10:36,524 --> 01:10:38,483
MAN [ON HOHO]:
Proceed to the highlighted route.

1472
01:10:38,650 --> 01:10:40,444
[IN WAVERING VOICE]
Proceed to the highlighted.

1473
01:10:41,945 --> 01:10:44,280
Just keep worrying
about Gwen.

1474
01:10:44,448 --> 01:10:47,533
I'll find a way there, boy.
Whatever it takes.

1475
01:10:47,952 --> 01:10:49,661
To Trelew!

1476
01:10:53,541 --> 01:10:54,373
Margaret.

1477
01:10:54,542 --> 01:10:56,417
Hand me my Me suit.

1478
01:10:56,586 --> 01:10:58,252
All sorted. Steve's, uh...

1479
01:10:58,421 --> 01:10:59,671
holding the fort

1480
01:10:59,838 --> 01:11:02,632
while I deliver the present, yes,

1481
01:11:02,800 --> 01:11:04,592
and find Arthur and Father.

1482
01:11:04,927 --> 01:11:06,011
Well done, dear.

1483
01:11:06,179 --> 01:11:09,890
Trelew's on a course of 187.7 degrees
from the geographic pole

1484
01:11:10,057 --> 01:11:11,766
but as it's the old sleigh,

1485
01:11:11,935 --> 01:11:14,560
allow a drift margin
of 1000 miles either side

1486
01:11:14,729 --> 01:11:17,064
of the meridian.
Got a sweater for Arthur,

1487
01:11:17,230 --> 01:11:18,398
your father's pills,

1488
01:11:18,565 --> 01:11:20,442
and some nice sweet tea.

1489
01:11:21,152 --> 01:11:22,109
Hm.

1490
01:11:22,694 --> 01:11:23,904
[CRASH]

1491
01:11:26,908 --> 01:11:28,033
COMPUTER:
Curtains.

1492
01:11:31,119 --> 01:11:32,703
S-1 dented.
PETER: Sir. Sir!

1493
01:11:32,872 --> 01:11:33,537
Big scratch

1494
01:11:33,706 --> 01:11:34,622
down side.

1495
01:11:34,791 --> 01:11:37,042
"Popped out to take present.

1496
01:11:37,377 --> 01:11:39,336
Turkey sandwich in fridge.
Mum and Dad."

1497
01:11:39,503 --> 01:11:40,837
Espresso machine broken.

1498
01:11:41,005 --> 01:11:43,297
That idiot, Arthur. He's sent

1499
01:11:43,466 --> 01:11:44,925
everyone crazy.

1500
01:11:45,092 --> 01:11:46,426
He'll destroy Christmas.

1501
01:11:46,594 --> 01:11:49,095
And you'll never
get to be Santa.

1502
01:11:50,347 --> 01:11:52,265
Steven!

1503
01:11:52,600 --> 01:11:53,850
I, um...

1504
01:11:54,268 --> 01:11:57,311
23 Mimosa Avenue, Trelew.

1505
01:11:58,230 --> 01:11:58,896
Malcolm,

1506
01:11:59,064 --> 01:12:01,358
there's no harm in using a manual.

1507
01:12:01,525 --> 01:12:04,277
Men.
Margaret, I order you to disembark.

1508
01:12:04,444 --> 01:12:05,737
It's not safe. Unh!

1509
01:12:05,904 --> 01:12:08,948
Piffle. I did a microlight flying course
on the Internet.

1510
01:12:09,117 --> 01:12:11,033
It can't be that different.

1511
01:12:11,868 --> 01:12:13,869
Oh! Steve.

1512
01:12:14,747 --> 01:12:17,623
You've dented it!
You take it out without asking?

1513
01:12:17,792 --> 01:12:19,626
Malcolm, you told me
he knew.

1514
01:12:19,793 --> 01:12:21,837
You know how Steve feels
about his S-1.

1515
01:12:22,005 --> 01:12:24,422
It's my S-1. S for "Santa."

1516
01:12:24,590 --> 01:12:26,591
I'm flying to this child.

1517
01:12:26,759 --> 01:12:30,220
Of course she's all that matters.
Not me, your son.

1518
01:12:30,387 --> 01:12:32,555
Not the 2 billion things
I did right tonight.

1519
01:12:32,724 --> 01:12:34,015
No!

1520
01:12:35,100 --> 01:12:37,394
This is about that pool table,
isn't it?

1521
01:12:37,561 --> 01:12:40,271
I told you, you should've written
to me.

1522
01:12:40,439 --> 01:12:42,733
I was 8. You're my dad!

1523
01:12:42,899 --> 01:12:43,942
For goodness sake!

1524
01:12:44,109 --> 01:12:46,028
Arthur and Grandsanta are out there

1525
01:12:46,194 --> 01:12:48,363
probably not wearing
nearly enough layers

1526
01:12:48,530 --> 01:12:51,365
and you two are bickering over
a big red toy?!

1527
01:12:51,533 --> 01:12:53,493
I'm not bickering.
If Steven could just

1528
01:12:53,661 --> 01:12:54,536
stand back-- Ooh!

1529
01:12:54,912 --> 01:12:56,203
COMPUTER:
Air bag.

1530
01:13:02,670 --> 01:13:04,546
You drive, Steven.

1531
01:13:05,172 --> 01:13:06,213
